			<div class="content" id="post-content-1694422">
									

<p>Fun fact: Alai LoCaen sen’a LoCaen Jaie is equivalent to &quot;Alai LoCaen, second daughter of Jaie, the head of the LoCaen family&quot;. Familial inheritance, and the right to use the family name as the primary name, is passed to the first born daughter of the family (So Alai's elder sister who is not mentioned in this series at all is LoCaen-tabi Uyatn sen'ou LoCaen Jaie). If there are no daughters, it will traditionally be passed to the wife of the eldest son.</p>
<p>Can you tell I like writing stuff like this? I really like writing stuff like this.</p>
<p>e: You know how sometimes a character just clicks for you? This was one of those times.</p>

