		<div class="post" id="post-1694918">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,1694918)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-1694918">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djoric" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(388108); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=388108&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227600" alt="Djoric" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=388108)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djoric" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(388108); return false;" >Djoric</a></span> <span class="odate time_1359139356 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">25 Jan 2013 18:42</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1694918">
									

<p>Thank y'kindly. I thoroughly enjoyed writing it.</p>
<p>Commentary time!</p>
<p>Alai was one of those characters where the image just popped into my head. Female character, had to have the RBY color scheme. Things just went from there. I figured that the group needed someone younger, a little naive, someone to embody the whole &quot;Oh my Empress we are going to <em>another universe</em>!&quot; part of life. Because let's be honest, the Foundation universe is filled with a bunch of jaded old scabs numbed by horror and all manner of bizarre and unnatural circumstances. Something as simple as homesickness is a nice change of pace for me.</p>
<p>Ed&#8230;Ed just sorta happened. All I knew was that the door had to be opened by a grumpy guy who had been there all night, jotted down some adjectives, and thought &quot;yeah, he sounds like an Ed.&quot; And, he can provide a good foil for Alai in the future: lazy and bored to her excited and enthusiastic. I find that I tend to do feature power duos /those two guys (See: Mary-Ann and Salah) often, mainly because it's just fun to see what you can make from just playing their personalities off of each other. Or maybe I just like writing about people being bros. Funnily enough, Alai and Lucrezen are also intended as foils, so you'll get to see how that works in the future too.</p>
<p>Quail is, for all intents and purposes, a self insert. (I justify his use in that Troy used him first. I just decided that he got fed up with how &quot;Djoric&quot; sounded and Human Resources <em>finally</em> authorized a name change). Pretty much me in twenty years, exaggerated a bit (or a lot, that's up for you to determine), with some personality from a professor I know mixed in (seriously, that guy is a ninja of the most scattered brain).</p>

							</div>

								
