															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jukse" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1433010); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1433010&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227600" alt="Jukse" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1433010)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/jukse" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1433010); return false;" >Jukse</a></span> <span class="odate time_1359427709 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">29 Jan 2013 02:48</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1697516">
									

<p>A nice and quite unexpected follow up to Last Plane Out of the South. I must confess that I didn't see Alai as much more than the &quot;curious girl&quot; of the group initially, but she does stand out here, and indeed leaves the role of somebody that is merely trying to adapt to an unfamiliar situation in favor of that of a person determined to accomplish what she set out to achieve, without losing her inherent light-hearted nature during the process.</p>
<p>I can't say that I have strong feeling for Ed one way or the other, but Quail did pick my interest besides his rather brieft appearance, and I'll be looking forward to which role he'll play from now on.</p>

							</div>

								
